researching other user researchers at Deloitte to understand how they do their Discovery process

That's a great approach to learn more about the Discovery process used by user researchers at Deloitte. Understanding how others in the field approach their work can provide valuable insights and inspiration. As you delve into this research, are there specific aspects of the Discovery process that you are particularly interested in exploring or any specific challenges you hope to address by learning from the experiences of others at Deloitte?

I am interested in understanding their process how they plan and conduct their research initiatives and then what are their biggest pain points so far it seems to do recruiting is a big one but everybody talks real users and they generate lots and lots of transcripts and then they have various ways of managing those transcripts we're trying to learn how a team manages transcripts and how we can improve on that process and then further we want to take and now analyzing those transcripts and build AI tools that will help assist with Insight generation and findings and repeatability

As part of your interest in understanding how user researchers at Deloitte plan and conduct their research initiatives, it's crucial to also consider the aspect of data analysis and deriving insights from the collected transcripts. Could you share more about the specific tools or techniques that interest you in analyzing transcripts and how you envision leveraging AI to enhance the process of generating insights and ensuring repeatability in your research efforts? Additionally, are there any particular challenges you anticipate in integrating AI tools into the analysis phase of your research projects?
